href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ixu1665702920696.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ixu1665702920696.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ixu1665702920696.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ixu1665702920696\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Key Validation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface recognizes primary keys, candidate keys, and index keys. Uniface always validates primary keys, but validation of candidate and index keys depends on the declarative and procedural constraints.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__section_w4486ab1b5b1_w4487ab1b5_w4488ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__section_w4489ab1b5b3_w4490ab1b5_w4491ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153337e56\">\n                       \n Candidate Keys\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45245e1_d45246e1_d45247e1\">When defining a candidate key, you can use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Validate</span> property to determine how Uniface validates the candidate key at run time. If Validate is <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, Uniface applies the same validation checks to the candidate key as are applied to primary keys. In forms, it activates the leaveModifiedKey trigger as appropriate in interactive sessions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45248e1_d45249e1_d45250e1\">If <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Validate</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>, Uniface ignores the candidate key during the validateKey process.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45251e1_d45252e1_d45253e1\">By default, Uniface set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Validate</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> for newly-defined candidate keys.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__section_w4492ab1b5b5_w4493ab1b5_w4494ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153337e89\">\n                       \n Indexes\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45257e1_d45258e1_d45259e1\">Indexes in Uniface are used to improve performance when searching for data in a database. They do not have to be unique. Uniface does not apply specific validation checks to indexes, although the following key-related validation functions also apply to indexes:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22490e1_d22491e1_d22492e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upd1665702601935.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upd1665702601935.html\" title=\"Return the type of the specified key.\">$keytype</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22493e1_d22494e1_d22495e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dmp1665702603557.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dmp1665702603557.html\" title=\"Return a list of the fields that make up a primary or candidate key or index.\">$keyfields</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__section_w4495ab1b5b7_w4496ab1b5_w4497ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153337e121\">\n                       \n Validating a Key\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45263e1_d45264e1_d45265e1\">Key validation can be initiated in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22496e1_d22497e1_d22498e1\">By an event that changes focus, such as going\n               from a key field to a non-key field<span class=\"ph\"> with\n                  the ^NEXT_FIELD structure editor function, prior to the leaveModifiedKey\n                  trigger</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22499e1_d22500e1_d22501e1\">As part of the validation of a higher level.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45266e1_d45267e1_d45268e1\">The condition for key validation is either one of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22502e1_d22503e1_d22504e1\">A key field has been modified, and the key has\n               not yet been validated successfully. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22505e1_d22506e1_d22507e1\">Validation is demanded for a key by setting\n                  \n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flp1665702599747.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flp1665702599747.html\" title=\"Indicate whether a specified primary or candidate key should be validated.\">$keycheck</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__section_w4498ab1b5b9_w4499ab1b5_w4500ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1153337e161\">\n                       \n Validation Process\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__p_d45272e1_d45273e1_d45274e1\">The process for validating a key is as follows:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22508e1_d22509e1_d22510e1\">Uniface validates all fields that are part of the key.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22511e1_d22512e1_d22513e1\">If the key is a compound key, Uniface checks that the key is complete.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ixu1665702920696__li_d22514e1_d22515e1_d22516e1\">Uniface activates the validateKey trigger.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Key Validation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Key Validation Uniface recognizes primary keys, candidate keys, and index keys. Uniface always validates primary keys, but validation of candidate and index keys depends on the declarative and procedural constraints. Candidate Keys When defining a candidate key, you can use the Validate property to determine how Uniface validates the candidate key at run time. If Validate is True , Uniface applies the same validation checks to the candidate key as are applied to primary keys. In forms, it activates the leaveModifiedKey trigger as appropriate in interactive sessions. If Validate is False , Uniface ignores the candidate key during the validateKey process. By default, Uniface set Validate to True for newly-defined candidate keys. Indexes Indexes in Uniface are used to improve performance when searching for data in a database. They do not have to be unique. Uniface does not apply specific validation checks to indexes, although the following key-related validation functions also apply to indexes: $keytype $keyfields Validating a Key Key validation can be initiated in the following ways: By an event that changes focus, such as going from a key field to a non-key field with the ^NEXT_FIELD structure editor function, prior to the leaveModifiedKey trigger . As part of the validation of a higher level. The condition for key validation is either one of the following: A key field has been modified, and the key has not yet been validated successfully. Validation is demanded for a key by setting $keycheck . Validation Process The process for validating a key is as follows: Uniface validates all fields that are part of the key. If the key is a compound key, Uniface checks that the key is complete. Uniface activates the validateKey trigger. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}